Response ID: resp_1122
Response Text: Do not be afraid to make some people unhappy.  Cultural funding is for cultural work.  Those that don't understand the value of cultural work may feel like they are "creative" and deserve to get public money, but we need to raise the bar for what constitutes the type of cultural work that is worthy of government financial support.  For example, why should public money fund crafts markets for jewelry, candle and soap makers, etc.  These are commercial endeavors to sell consumer goods, with many options to reach buyers, and no lack of soap, candles or jewelry in hundreds of shops literally all over Austin.  They should not be getting public subsidies.  On the other hand, Queer Black Feminist theatre is not common at all and should be supported by public funds.

